255
00:15:59.612 --> 00:16:03.072
or older children, to support drug effectiveness

256
00:16:03.532 --> 00:16:06.832
and use in the pediatric population when there's

257
00:16:07.012 --> 00:16:10.952
sufficient similarity in disease, drug pharmacology,

258
00:16:11.392 --> 00:16:15.182
and response to treatment, such that we don't need to repeat the

259
00:16:15.312 --> 00:16:19.192
full efficacy trials in the pediatric population to

260
00:16:19.252 --> 00:16:20.572
improve efficiency.

261
00:16:21.412 --> 00:16:21.992
To support

262
00:16:22.792 --> 00:16:26.072
these three core similarities and in turn

263
00:16:26.112 --> 00:16:29.482
extrapolation, mechanistic understanding and

264
00:16:29.572 --> 00:16:33.492
quantitative modeling using relevant surrogates

265
00:16:33.532 --> 00:16:36.812
such as drug exposure and pharmacodynamic

266
00:16:36.912 --> 00:16:40.012
response to demonstrate sufficient

267
00:16:40.072 --> 00:16:43.972
similarity after treatment between the pediatric and the

268
00:16:44.032 --> 00:16:47.072
