439
00:27:18.476 --> 00:27:20.616
Good afternoon. My name is Nicole Dresner.

440
00:27:20.716 --> 00:27:24.456
I am a pediatric oncologist and Deputy Director of the Division of Oncology

441
00:27:24.536 --> 00:27:25.516
2 at the FDA.

442
00:27:26.416 --> 00:27:29.886
I'll be speaking about a recent example of pediatric

443
00:27:29.936 --> 00:27:31.726
extrapolation from my division,

444
00:27:32.596 --> 00:27:36.556
in the 2024 approval of Lutathera for adolescents with somatostatin

445
00:27:36.636 --> 00:27:40.256
receptor positive gastroenteropancreatic neuroendocrine

446
00:27:40.296 --> 00:27:41.936
tumors, or GEP-NETs.

447
00:27:42.796 --> 00:27:46.136
Our review and approval applied the principles of the

448
00:27:46.176 --> 00:27:49.876
extrapolation framework that you heard about in the previous two presentations.

449
00:27:50.936 --> 00:27:54.836
GEP-NETs are a clinically heterogeneous spectrum of tumors arising from

450
00:27:54.896 --> 00:27:58.496
neuroendocrine cells in the GI tract, pancreas, bile duct, and

451
00:27:58.536 --> 00:28:02.476
gallbladder, and express the somatostatin receptor in over 90% of

452
00:28:02.576 --> 00:28:06.276
cases. In the US, approximately 200 adolescents are

453
00:28:06.316 --> 00:28:08.036
diagnosed with GEP-NET per year.

454
00:28:08.936 --> 00:28:12.836
Metastatic GEP-NET is characterized by an indolent disease course but with an

455
00:28:12.916 --> 00:28:16.656
overall poor prognosis. And prior to 2024, there were

456
00:28:16.696 --> 00:28:20.456
no approved therapies for pediatric patients, though off-label use

457
00:28:20.496 --> 00:28:22.646
according to adult treatment paradigms is

458
00:28:22.676 --> 00:28:26.126
common. As you heard, one of the major

459
00:28:26.155 --> 00:28:30.045
considerations for the use of extrapolation is whether the adult and

460
00:28:30.076 --> 00:28:33.916
pediatric disease are sufficiently similar to allow for comparison

461
00:28:33.936 --> 00:28:37.806
and use of adult data. There are some notable differences

462
00:28:37.816 --> 00:28:41.556
in GEP-NETs between adolescents and adults, namely that pediatric

463
00:28:41.566 --> 00:28:45.466
GEP-NETs are predominantly Grades 1 or 2, with a fewer proportion

464
00:28:45.516 --> 00:28:47.846
of Grade 3 patients compared to adults,

465
00:28:48.716 --> 00:28:52.356
and a comparatively high proportion of pediatric GEP-NETs are

466
00:28:52.396 --> 00:28:55.676
associated with hereditary cancer predisposition syndromes,

467
00:28:56.076 --> 00:28:59.916
namely MEN 1, Von Hippel-Lindau, NF1, and Tuberous Sclerosis

468
00:28:59.926 --> 00:29:03.896
Complex. However, importantly, for this application for an

469
00:29:03.976 --> 00:29:07.866
SSTR targeting therapy, SSTR expression is a

470
00:29:07.876 --> 00:29:10.656
clinically relevant biomarker across all age groups.

471
00:29:11.196 --> 00:29:15.076
Although historical data in adolescents are limited due to the disease

472
00:29:15.176 --> 00:29:18.956
rarity, a high prevalence of SSTR expression in Grades 1 to

473
00:29:19.076 --> 00:29:22.216
2 GEP-NETs is described in registries and the

474
00:29:22.256 --> 00:29:26.076
literature. Therefore, somatostatin analog and targeted

475
00:29:26.096 --> 00:29:29.996
peptide receptor radionuclide therapies are a feasible approach to treatment in

476
00:29:30.056 --> 00:29:30.796
adolescents.

477
00:29:32.916 --> 00:29:36.736
Lutathera is a radiolabeled somatostatin analog that was initially

478
00:29:36.776 --> 00:29:39.686
approved in 2018 for the treatment of adults with

479
00:29:39.836 --> 00:29:43.816
SSTR-positive GEP-NETs based on the results of the NETTER-1

480
00:29:43.976 --> 00:29:47.876
study. NETTER-1 was an international randomized controlled trial of

481
00:29:47.896 --> 00:29:51.616
Lutathera plus long-acting octreotide versus long-acting

482
00:29:51.636 --> 00:29:55.356
octreotide in 229 adults with well-differentiated

483
00:29:55.396 --> 00:29:58.936
metastatic midgut tumors. The primary endpoint of

484
00:29:59.276 --> 00:30:02.766
blinded independent centrally reviewed assessed progression-free survival, or

485
00:30:02.876 --> 00:30:06.756
PFS, demonstrated a statistically significant improvement

486
00:30:06.796 --> 00:30:10.516
with Lutathera treatment with a hazard ratio of 0.21.

487
00:30:10.976 --> 00:30:14.896
Notably, the ORR, overall response rate, was 13% in the

488
00:30:14.916 --> 00:30:18.736
Lutathera arm.Given that there were no approved therapies for

489
00:30:18.796 --> 00:30:22.776
adolescent patients with GEP-NETs, the FDA issued a written request in

490
00:30:22.896 --> 00:30:26.646
2020 for a pediatric study to provide evidence for the safe and

491
00:30:26.676 --> 00:30:30.396
effective use of Lutathera in this population, and the NETTER-P

492
00:30:30.456 --> 00:30:32.416
study was initiated in 2022.

493
00:30:34.296 --> 00:30:37.576
NETTER-P is an international multicenter single-arm study

494
00:30:37.996 --> 00:30:41.646
enrolling adolescents with SSTR-positive GEP-NETs or

495
00:30:41.796 --> 00:30:44.846
pheochromocytoma paraganglioma, or PPGLs.

496
00:30:45.496 --> 00:30:49.116
PPGLs are rare neuroendocrine tumors arising from the chromaffin

497
00:30:49.216 --> 00:30:52.836
cells of the adrenal medulla or sympathetic or parasympathetic

498
00:30:52.876 --> 00:30:56.856
ganglia that also express SSTR and were included to provide

499
00:30:56.916 --> 00:30:59.556
safety and dosimetry data for Lutathera in a broader

500
00:30:59.576 --> 00:31:03.556
population. The primary endpoints were target organ absorbed

501
00:31:03.696 --> 00:31:07.636
radiation doses and adverse events in laboratory toxicities in the

502
00:31:07.686 --> 00:31:11.596
pooled cohort of patients. Given the single-arm nature of the study

503
00:31:11.606 --> 00:31:15.046
and low projected enrollment due to the disease rarity, efficacy was

504
00:31:15.076 --> 00:31:17.056
evaluated as an exploratory endpoint.

505
00:31:17.716 --> 00:31:20.876
Enrolled patients received the approved dose and schedule of Lutathera.

506
00:31:22.616 --> 00:31:26.606
In total, safety was evaluated in nine patients enrolled on NETTER-P at the

507
00:31:26.676 --> 00:31:29.496
time of approval, including four patients with GEP-NET.

508
00:31:30.036 --> 00:31:33.616
The adverse event profile was similar to that observed in adults, with the most

509
00:31:33.656 --> 00:31:37.326
common observed adverse events and Grade 3 or higher adverse events being

510
00:31:37.336 --> 00:31:38.716
lymphopenia and neutropenia.

511
00:31:39.516 --> 00:31:41.836
The US Prescribing Information, or USPI,

512
00:31:42.816 --> 00:31:46.656
for Lutathera notes that the risk of radiation exposure associated with

513
00:31:46.696 --> 00:31:50.556
Lutathera are greater in pediatric patients than in adult patients due to

514
00:31:50.596 --> 00:31:54.416
their longer life expectancy, acknowledging the known long-term effects of

515
00:31:54.436 --> 00:31:56.796
radiation and radiopharmaceuticals.

516
00:31:57.736 --> 00:32:01.456
No clinically relevant difference in Lutathera exposure between NETTER-P

517
00:32:01.496 --> 00:32:04.896
patients and adults was observed, and the estimated radiation

518
00:32:04.976 --> 00:32:08.506
doses were largely similar between adults and

519
00:32:08.556 --> 00:32:12.496
pediatric patients, with one exception that I will discuss next.

520
00:32:12.506 --> 00:32:16.436
The study also reported a best response of stable disease across

521
00:32:16.476 --> 00:32:20.456
the pooled cohort of patients, though this was considered consistent with the adult

522
00:32:20.516 --> 00:32:24.116
experience, namely the ORR of 13% that was observed in the

523
00:32:24.156 --> 00:32:27.876
Lutathera arm of NETTER-1. One patient with GEP-NET had

524
00:32:27.896 --> 00:32:29.976
disease progression at 8.6 months.

525
00:32:31.856 --> 00:32:35.716
Dosimetry refers to the determination and measurement of the amount or

526
00:32:35.836 --> 00:32:38.976
dose of radiation absorbed by organs throughout the body.

527
00:32:38.986 --> 00:32:42.946
As I mentioned, target organ dosimetry values were similar between adults and

528
00:32:42.996 --> 00:32:44.496
adolescents who received Lutathera.

529
00:32:45.245 --> 00:32:48.996
The dosimetry extrapolation model, which compared median dosimetry

530
00:32:49.096 --> 00:32:52.676
values with 5th and 95th percentiles, showed that neither

531
00:32:52.736 --> 00:32:56.536
kidney nor bone marrow estimates from adults with GEP-NET were affected by the

532
00:32:56.576 --> 00:33:00.476
addition of the pooled adolescent data, confirming the similar dosimetry

533
00:33:00.536 --> 00:33:01.956
estimates between the two groups.

534
00:33:02.796 --> 00:33:06.736
However, as shown in the top red box in the table on this slide, the

535
00:33:06.776 --> 00:33:10.636
observed probabilities of exceeding 29 gray for the kidneys and two

536
00:33:10.676 --> 00:33:14.506
gray for the bone marrow after four cycles of Lutathera did not

537
00:33:14.556 --> 00:33:18.136
exceed 20% in adolescents, which were the thresholds selected for the

538
00:33:18.146 --> 00:33:22.076
trial. The 29 gray threshold was selected based on published

539
00:33:22.116 --> 00:33:24.976
literature that noted no grade greater than three

540
00:33:25.116 --> 00:33:28.876
nephrotoxicity in 11 patients with kidney absorbed doses

541
00:33:28.916 --> 00:33:31.476
exceeding 28 gray after treatment with Lutathera.

542
00:33:32.216 --> 00:33:35.796
However, as shown in the bottom red box, the 95th percentile of the

543
00:33:35.816 --> 00:33:39.516
predicted probability of exceeding 29 gray for the kidneys in

544
00:33:39.596 --> 00:33:43.256
adolescents was higher than 20%. The confidence interval

545
00:33:43.336 --> 00:33:47.036
around the predicted probability is wide due to the small number of adolescent

546
00:33:47.136 --> 00:33:51.076
patients, and so these findings should be interpreted with caution.

547
00:33:51.096 --> 00:33:54.805
But late onset renal toxicity is a known risk of radiopharmaceuticals,

548
00:33:54.816 --> 00:33:58.636
including Lutathera. We consider this potential increased risk in

549
00:33:58.696 --> 00:34:02.566
adolescents in the context of the overall risk-benefit profile that was

550
00:34:02.576 --> 00:34:04.786
supported by a large PFS benefit in

551
00:34:04.816 --> 00:34:08.676
NETTER-1. Our key review questions focused

552
00:34:08.716 --> 00:34:12.406
on whether it is appropriate to extrapolate data from adult patients with

553
00:34:12.417 --> 00:34:15.877
GEP-NETs to adolescents and whether the safety and effectiveness of

554
00:34:15.897 --> 00:34:19.437
Lutathera in a rare pediatric population with limited data could be

555
00:34:19.476 --> 00:34:20.696
extrapolated from adults.

556
00:34:22.276 --> 00:34:26.176
As a reminder, the pediatric extrapolation framework requires assessment of the

557
00:34:26.216 --> 00:34:30.127
similarities and differences between the reference and target populations with

558
00:34:30.156 --> 00:34:34.116
respect to the disease, investigational drug pharmacology in response to

559
00:34:34.156 --> 00:34:37.935
treatment, an assessment of the available safety information, and an

560
00:34:37.995 --> 00:34:41.826
assessment of the gaps in knowledge for the extrapolated population and

561
00:34:41.877 --> 00:34:45.636
how this affects the confidence and uncertainties of the extrapolation concept.

562
00:34:47.627 --> 00:34:51.616
The FDA review team determined that extrapolation of adult

563
00:34:51.656 --> 00:34:55.496
data to adolescents with GEP-NETs was appropriate, and the totality of

564
00:34:55.516 --> 00:34:59.266
data across the adult and adolescent populations provided

565
00:34:59.266 --> 00:35:02.266
substantial evidence of safety and effectiveness of Lutathera for

566
00:35:02.316 --> 00:35:05.936
adolescents. This was based on the similarity of the disease,

567
00:35:05.956 --> 00:35:09.916
particularly in that the expected response to a targeted therapy was assumed to be

568
00:35:09.956 --> 00:35:13.586
the same in patients with SSTR expression, and that the

569
00:35:13.636 --> 00:35:17.256
exposure-response relationships for efficacy and safety were also

570
00:35:17.276 --> 00:35:20.976
expected to be similar. Given the extreme rarity of GEP-NETs in

571
00:35:21.016 --> 00:35:24.886
adolescent patients, a randomized controlled trial was considered infeasible,

572
00:35:25.256 --> 00:35:26.976
and since time to event endpoints are

573
00:35:27.996 --> 00:35:31.916
uninterpretable in single-arm trials, our assessment of efficacy

574
00:35:31.976 --> 00:35:35.896
was heavily extrapolated from the adult experience, including NETTER-1

575
00:35:35.916 --> 00:35:39.636
and supportive data from an expanded access study conducted in the Netherlands.

576
00:35:41.656 --> 00:35:45.426
The FDA review highlighted the similarities in safety, pharmacokinetics, and

577
00:35:45.476 --> 00:35:47.636
dosimetry assessments between the two groups.

578
00:35:48.036 --> 00:35:51.976
The large, clinically meaningful, and statistically robust PFS effect in adult

579
00:35:52.036 --> 00:35:55.656
patients treated with Lutathera on NETTER-1 provided strong

580
00:35:55.776 --> 00:35:59.496
evidence for the treatment's effectiveness and supported its extrapolation to a

581
00:35:59.536 --> 00:36:03.256
rare pediatric population with a high unmet need and no FDA-approved

582
00:36:03.266 --> 00:36:03.826
therapies.

583
00:36:06.156 --> 00:36:09.786
Given the relatively short safety follow-up for the NETTER-P study at the time of

584
00:36:09.876 --> 00:36:13.826
application submission, post-marketing requirements, or PMRs, for

585
00:36:13.856 --> 00:36:17.256
an evaluation of the two major long-term toxicities, renal

586
00:36:17.296 --> 00:36:21.176
failure and myelodysplastic syndrome and acute leukemias, were

587
00:36:21.236 --> 00:36:24.836
issued for the conduct of safety analyses after five and 10 years of

588
00:36:24.876 --> 00:36:28.496
follow-up. This data will augment our understanding of the safety

589
00:36:28.596 --> 00:36:32.286
profile of Lutathera in adolescent patients and provide necessary

590
00:36:32.316 --> 00:36:35.846
information on whether additional dose modifications or monitoring

591
00:36:35.876 --> 00:36:39.696
recommendations are warranted.The robust

592
00:36:39.756 --> 00:36:43.205
effect on PFS observed in the NETTER-1 trial provided a strong

593
00:36:43.276 --> 00:36:46.796
basis for considering extrapolation in this

594
00:36:46.836 --> 00:36:50.396
case. And the NETTER-P trial was able to provide important safety,

595
00:36:50.496 --> 00:36:54.326
dosimetry, and clinical pharmacology data in a small number of pediatric

596
00:36:54.396 --> 00:36:58.256
patients. Post-marketing requirements were issued for long-term

597
00:36:58.296 --> 00:37:02.176
safety follow-up. In summary, the approval of Lutathera for adolescents with

598
00:37:02.216 --> 00:37:05.806
GEPNETS is an example of the successful extrapolation of adult data to

599
00:37:05.876 --> 00:37:08.896
support a new indication in a rare pediatric disease.

600
00:37:10.096 --> 00:37:13.716
And I would like to thank the panel and the entire team at the FDA. Thanks.

601
00:37:23.336 --> 00:37:24.296
Hi, good afternoon.

602
00:37:25.736 --> 00:37:25.976
And

603
00:37:26.856 --> 00:37:28.976
thank you for the opportunity to speak here today.

604
00:37:29.896 --> 00:37:33.796
My name is Mansi Dalal. I'm a pediatric oncologist and a clinical reviewer

605
00:37:33.836 --> 00:37:36.596
in the Division of Hemomalignancies 1 at the FDA.

606
00:37:37.426 --> 00:37:41.316
And I will be giving our last presentation today, so stick with it.

607
00:37:42.356 --> 00:37:46.206
And I'll be discussing a case study to demonstrate the scientific and

608
00:37:46.276 --> 00:37:50.156
regulatory aspects of how pediatric

609
00:37:50.196 --> 00:37:53.996
extrapolation was leveraged in the clinical development program for blinatumomab.

610
00:37:58.236 --> 00:38:01.496
So B-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia or B-ALL,

611
00:38:02.436 --> 00:38:05.856
is the most common pediatric cancer and the second most common acute

612
00:38:05.896 --> 00:38:09.856
leukemia in adults, which if left untreated, is universally

613
00:38:09.896 --> 00:38:10.236
fatal.

614
00:38:11.176 --> 00:38:14.796
B-ALL originates in the bone marrow from the malignant transformation of

615
00:38:14.836 --> 00:38:18.716
progenitor B-cell lymphoid cells

616
00:38:18.736 --> 00:38:22.136
and can infiltrate the extra medullary spaces, including the peripheral blood,

617
00:38:22.636 --> 00:38:25.136
lymph nodes, the central nervous system, and the testicles.

618
00:38:26.076 --> 00:38:30.036
B-ALL is also characterized by uniform cell surface

619
00:38:30.046 --> 00:38:33.716
expression of CD19 in newly diagnosed

620
00:38:33.756 --> 00:38:37.316
patients and patients with relapse post-chemotherapy.

621
00:38:38.516 --> 00:38:42.316
The outcome of pediatric patients with B-ALL incrementally

622
00:38:42.336 --> 00:38:46.276
improved through the optimization of risk-stratified and risk-adapted

623
00:38:46.756 --> 00:38:50.216
treatment regimen, sequential combinations of multiphasic

624
00:38:50.336 --> 00:38:54.296
cytotoxic chemotherapy, and central nervous system prophylaxis.

625
00:38:54.736 --> 00:38:57.556
However, relapse, and long-term and late

626
00:38:57.636 --> 00:39:01.556
toxicities of cytotoxic therapies continue to remain a major

627
00:39:01.596 --> 00:39:02.036
challenge.

628
00:39:02.976 --> 00:39:06.565
The current treatment paradigm of ALL in both adults and

629
00:39:06.656 --> 00:39:09.616
children entail three phases: induction,

630
00:39:09.856 --> 00:39:11.326
consolidation, and maintenance.

631
00:39:12.196 --> 00:39:16.016
While the specific combination of therapies used may be different, the

632
00:39:16.056 --> 00:39:19.736
goals of each phase are similar in adults and pediatric patients.

633
00:39:19.876 --> 00:39:23.596
In general, the goal of induction phase is to achieve complete remission,

634
00:39:24.216 --> 00:39:27.516
and the goal of consolidation and maintenance phases is to maintain

635
00:39:27.576 --> 00:39:29.996
remission and improve overall survival.

636
00:39:32.776 --> 00:39:36.716
Blinatumomab is a bispecific CD19-directed CD3

637
00:39:36.756 --> 00:39:40.516
T-cell engager. It forms a synapse between CD3 T cells

638
00:39:40.816 --> 00:39:44.436
and CD19 positive target cells, leading to

639
00:39:44.496 --> 00:39:48.276
upregulation of cell adhesion molecules and production

640
00:39:48.636 --> 00:39:52.396
of cytolytic proteins, release of inflammatory cytokines,

641
00:39:52.936 --> 00:39:56.856
leading to redirected lysis of CD19 positive target

642
00:39:56.936 --> 00:39:59.476
cells, including B-cell ALL blasts.

643
00:40:00.516 --> 00:40:04.416
Currently, blinatumomab is dose-fixed or BSA-based and given as a

644
00:40:04.656 --> 00:40:08.326
28-day continuous intravenous infusion followed by

645
00:40:08.716 --> 00:40:10.216
two weeks of treatment-free period.

646
00:40:11.156 --> 00:40:15.096
The exact dosing, including the use of step dosing, depends on

647
00:40:15.116 --> 00:40:16.976
the indication it is being used for.

648
00:40:18.196 --> 00:40:21.376
Cytokine release syndrome and neurological toxicities,

649
00:40:21.476 --> 00:40:24.916
including immune effector cell-associated neurotoxicity

650
00:40:24.976 --> 00:40:28.436
syndrome or ICANS, are two serious safety risks

651
00:40:28.496 --> 00:40:32.276
associated with blinatumomab, for which there is a box warning in the

652
00:40:32.396 --> 00:40:35.076
US prescribing information or USPI.

653
00:40:35.936 --> 00:40:37.616
Other adverse reactions include

654
00:40:39.016 --> 00:40:42.956
infusion-related reactions, infections, tumor lysis syndrome,

655
00:40:43.196 --> 00:40:46.806
neutropenia, febrile neutropenia, and elevated liver enzymes.

656
00:40:49.416 --> 00:40:53.076
So let's discuss how pediatric extrapolation framework, which you heard from Lauren

657
00:40:53.136 --> 00:40:56.576
earlier today, would be applied to blinatumomab.

658
00:40:57.456 --> 00:41:00.936
The main components of the extrapolation concept are to determine the

659
00:41:01.896 --> 00:41:05.806
similarities and differences in the disease, the drug pharmacology,

660
00:41:05.836 --> 00:41:09.106
response to treatment, and safety between the adult and pediatric

661
00:41:09.156 --> 00:41:12.626
population with CD19 positive B-cell ALL.

662
00:41:13.936 --> 00:41:17.746
For CD19 positive B-cell ALL, a very high degree of

663
00:41:17.796 --> 00:41:21.156
disease similarities between adult and pediatric population exists,

664
00:41:21.516 --> 00:41:25.056
including the pathophysiology, the course of the disease, and the

665
00:41:25.116 --> 00:41:26.656
diagnostic criteria used.

666
00:41:27.456 --> 00:41:31.416
Furthermore, CD19 expression, which is very relevant to a

667
00:41:31.456 --> 00:41:35.156
CD19-directed therapy such as blinatumomab, is similar

668
00:41:35.636 --> 00:41:39.056
in both adult and pediatric populations and expressed

669
00:41:39.076 --> 00:41:42.806
uniformly on the leukemic blasts in the newly diagnosed and

670
00:41:42.916 --> 00:41:45.396
post-chemotherapy relapse disease states.

671
00:41:46.916 --> 00:41:50.356
Next, the cellular level mechanism of blinatumomab is not

672
00:41:50.416 --> 00:41:53.776
affected by age, growth, and hormonal status.

673
00:41:54.396 --> 00:41:57.576
And in fact, T cell, B cell, CD3, and

674
00:41:57.636 --> 00:42:00.316
CD19 are present and functional

675
00:42:01.456 --> 00:42:04.096
from infancy to older age.

676
00:42:05.116 --> 00:42:08.696
Finally, the anticipated exposure-response relationship

677
00:42:09.036 --> 00:42:12.276
between the pediatric and adult patients was

678
00:42:12.316 --> 00:42:16.126
postulated to be similar, meaning that

679
00:42:16.136 --> 00:42:19.606
because of similarity in the disease and the mechanism of action,

680
00:42:19.916 --> 00:42:23.676
achieving a similar drug exposure in pediatric patients

681
00:42:23.736 --> 00:42:26.936
would lead to a similar clinical response when compared to

682
00:42:26.996 --> 00:42:28.516
adults.

683
00:42:30.116 --> 00:42:32.956
This slide provides an overview of the blinatumomab approvals.

684
00:42:33.356 --> 00:42:37.186
Pediatric extrapolation was utilized throughout the entire clinical

685
00:42:37.256 --> 00:42:40.996
development program for blinatumomab.Blinatumomab was

686
00:42:41.036 --> 00:42:44.856
initially approved in 2014 under the Accelerated Approval Pathway for

687
00:42:44.916 --> 00:42:48.216
patients with relapsed/refractory Philadelphia chromosome-negative

688
00:42:48.936 --> 00:42:52.856
ALL weighing at least 45 kilograms based on the endpoint of complete

689
00:42:52.936 --> 00:42:56.476
remission and complete remission with incomplete hematologic recovery

690
00:42:56.836 --> 00:42:57.716
with durability.

691
00:42:58.556 --> 00:43:02.496
This initial study established the efficacy and safety of blinatumomab

692
00:43:02.556 --> 00:43:02.636
in

693
00:43:03.696 --> 00:43:07.316
monotherapy in the source population, the adult patients, in the

694
00:43:07.356 --> 00:43:08.676
relapsed/refractory setting.

695
00:43:09.816 --> 00:43:12.556
At the time of this approval, a dedicated pediatric study,

696
00:43:12.976 --> 00:43:16.156
MT103205, was underway, which was a

697
00:43:16.236 --> 00:43:19.916
dose-finding and dose expansion study to evaluate BSA-based

698
00:43:19.926 --> 00:43:23.876
dosing, safety, tolerability, and antitumor activity in

699
00:43:23.916 --> 00:43:27.696
children less than 18 years of age with relapsed/refractory

700
00:43:27.776 --> 00:43:28.676
B-cell ALL.

701
00:43:29.476 --> 00:43:33.336
The study demonstrated that blinatumomab was well-tolerated, with

702
00:43:33.396 --> 00:43:36.696
lower incidences of neurological toxicities and similar

703
00:43:37.016 --> 00:43:40.036
cytokine release syndrome rates in children compared to the adults.

704
00:43:40.725 --> 00:43:44.516
Thus, BSA-based dosing of blinatumomab was approved for patients

705
00:43:44.555 --> 00:43:47.746
who were weighing under 45 kilos with

706
00:43:47.756 --> 00:43:51.376
relapsed/refractory Philadelphia chromosome-negative ALL, and the

707
00:43:51.416 --> 00:43:52.756
primary efficacy results

708
00:43:53.636 --> 00:43:57.536
from the study 205 was also included in the US prescribing

709
00:43:57.596 --> 00:44:00.036
information in 2016.

710
00:44:01.476 --> 00:44:05.376
Next, in 2018, blinatumomab was approved for treatment of ALL

711
00:44:05.416 --> 00:44:09.356
in the first or second remission with minimal residual disease under the

712
00:44:09.396 --> 00:44:13.116
Accelerated Approval Pathway. The basis of approval was the

713
00:44:13.136 --> 00:44:13.836
BLAST study,

714
00:44:15.376 --> 00:44:19.176
which was a single-arm study of adults greater than or equal to 18 years.

715
00:44:19.936 --> 00:44:23.796
Eighty-one percent of patients achieved MRD negativity after one cycle

716
00:44:23.956 --> 00:44:27.716
of blinatumomab. Note that there were no pediatric patients

717
00:44:27.836 --> 00:44:31.716
enrolled on the BLAST study. Efficacy to the pediatric patients

718
00:44:31.756 --> 00:44:35.496
was extrapolated from this adequate and well-controlled study

719
00:44:35.556 --> 00:44:38.236
in adults with MRD positive B-cell ALL.

720
00:44:39.176 --> 00:44:42.896
And safety was known from a adequate and well-controlled study in

721
00:44:42.976 --> 00:44:46.516
pediatric patients with relapsed/refractory B-cell ALL, the study

722
00:44:46.716 --> 00:44:50.336
205, as I discussed earlier. Thus, the conclusion was to grant an

723
00:44:50.396 --> 00:44:54.036
age-agnostic indication for MRD positive B-cell ALL.

724
00:44:55.356 --> 00:44:59.016
Finally, in 2014, blinatumomab was approved for the

725
00:44:59.056 --> 00:45:02.996
treatment of Philadelphia chromosome negative B-cell ALL in consolidation

726
00:45:03.056 --> 00:45:06.556
phase with multi-phase chemotherapy in adults and children.

727
00:45:07.096 --> 00:45:10.876
Let's discuss how extrapolation was utilized in this setting in more

728
00:45:10.916 --> 00:45:11.296
detail.

729
00:45:13.306 --> 00:45:17.266
The basis of approval for consolidation indication of blinatumomab in the

730
00:45:17.316 --> 00:45:21.156
context of multi-phase chemotherapy was based on three randomized

731
00:45:21.196 --> 00:45:22.096
control trials

732
00:45:22.976 --> 00:45:26.216
and a supportive meta-analysis that was conducted by the FDA.

733
00:45:26.656 --> 00:45:30.476
In all studies, patient received blinatumomab after induction phase

734
00:45:32.436 --> 00:45:33.776
with chemotherapy

735
00:45:34.976 --> 00:45:36.416
that they received afterwards.

736
00:45:37.636 --> 00:45:41.296
Study E1910 was a randomized study to compare overall

737
00:45:41.396 --> 00:45:45.316
survival between blinatumomab and chemotherapy versus chemotherapy

738
00:45:45.396 --> 00:45:48.616
alone in both MRD positive and MRD

739
00:45:48.676 --> 00:45:52.496
negative disease states in adults 30 to 70 years of age

740
00:45:52.796 --> 00:45:55.296
with Philadelphia chromosome negative B-cell ALL.

741
00:45:55.976 --> 00:45:59.616
The MRD arm showed that intercalating blinatumomab and

742
00:45:59.656 --> 00:46:03.376
chemotherapy led to a survival benefit and established

743
00:46:03.416 --> 00:46:07.336
efficacy and safety of blinatumomab in the consolidation phase within

744
00:46:07.376 --> 00:46:10.096
the context of multi-phase chemotherapy in adults.

745
00:46:11.216 --> 00:46:14.876
The study 201/20215 was also a

746
00:46:14.916 --> 00:46:18.696
randomized study of patients 28 days old to 18

747
00:46:18.716 --> 00:46:22.256
years with first relapse of Philadelphia chromosome negative B-cell

748
00:46:22.376 --> 00:46:26.156
ALL. FDA performed a descriptive analysis of overall

749
00:46:26.216 --> 00:46:30.146
survival, or OS, and post hoc analysis of relapse-free

750
00:46:30.236 --> 00:46:33.396
survival, or RFS, which showed a survival benefit.

751
00:46:34.756 --> 00:46:38.476
And finally, study AALL 1331 was a

752
00:46:38.536 --> 00:46:42.476
cooperative group randomized study of chemotherapy and blinatumomab

753
00:46:42.756 --> 00:46:46.456
versus chemotherapy alone and enrolled patients with low risk or high

754
00:46:46.536 --> 00:46:49.676
risk B-cell ALL after first relapse.

